\subsection{Geometric Analysis of the Road Obstacle}
The bump can be characterized as a sinusoidal undulate. With a maximum amplitude corresponding to the maximum height $h$ of the bump, and a lenght of $2L$ . The equation can be expressed by simple geometry by:
\begin{equation} Bump(x)=A\sin{P x}\end{equation}.  Where P is the period of the sinusoidal function

